<page build="">
    <shortlink>getting started testing</shortlink>
    <topic>Testing</topic>
    <description title=""></description>
    <sections>
        <section>
            <title>Preview your Application</title>
            <description>
                <p>Let's preview our application within Alpha Anywhere using Working Preview to verify that it works. Working Preview simulates a browser, letting you test your application in the development environment without needing to publish it to a server.</p>
            </description>
            <steps>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Click "Working Preview". Working Preview </p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/preview1.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>You will see the button. It will appear as teal text against a white background.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/preview2.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Click the button to display the "Hello, world!" message.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/preview3.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
            </steps>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Run your app on a Mobile Device</title>
            <description>
                <p>Now that we've tested our application, let's try it out on a mobile device.</p>
            </description>
            <steps>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Return to the Design tab.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest1.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Click "Remote Test". Remote Test let's you test your app on other devices without needing to publish your application to a server.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest2.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Start the development server when prompted. Select "Yes" and click "OK".</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest3.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Click "Remote Test" again and select "Full Preview".</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest4.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Select "QR Code" and click "OK".</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest5.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Scan the QR Code with your mobile device. Your computer and mobile device must be on the same wifi network.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest6.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Open the link in a browser on your device.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest7.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <description>
                        <p>Tap the "Hello" button to display the message.</p>
                    </description>
                    <figure>
                        <link>images/remoteTest8.png</link>
                    </figure>
                </step>
            </steps>
        </section>
        <section>
            <description>
                <p>Congratulations! Now that you understand the basics of creating a workspace, adding a component, and adding controls and events to create an app, you're ready to start building applications in Alpha Anywhere.</p>
                <p>We recommend taking the Alpha 304: Community Edition Introduction next. Click the button below to enroll in the free course.</p>
            </description>
        </section>
    </sections>
